===Noun===
{{en-noun|chairmen}}

# A person presiding over a meeting.
# The head of a [[corporate]] or [[government]]al [[board of directors]], a committee, or other formal entity.
# {{lb|en|historical}} Someone whose job is to [[carry]] people in a portable [[chair]], [[sedan chair]], or similar conveyance.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1749|author=Henry Fielding|title=Tom Jones|publisher=Folio Society|year_published=1973|page=618|passage=Mr Western entered; but not before a small wrangling bout had passed between him and his '''chairmen'''; for the fellows, who had taken up their burden at the Hercules Pillars, had conceived no hopes of having any future good customer in the squire {{...}}}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1836|author=Charles Dickens|title=The Pickwick Papers|passage=Mr. Winkle, catching sight of a lady's face at the window of the sedan, turned hastily round, plied the knocker with all his might and main, and called frantically upon the '''chairman''' to take the chair away again.}}

====Usage notes====
* Historically this term denoted a man, but it is now also used for women.

